request.description:
The `GET` request to `/public/allergies` endpoint retrieves a list of allergies available in the system.

### Response

The response will be a JSON object with the following properties:

- `status` (string): Represents the status of the response.

- `data` (array): An array of objects containing allergy information. Each object has the following properties:

    - `id` (number): The unique identifier of the allergy.

    - `name` (string): The name of the allergy.

- `message` (string): Represents any additional message related to the response.


#### JSON Schema

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "status": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "id": {
            "type": "number"
          },
          "name": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

